{"word":"κλῆσις","slug":"κλῆσις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κλῆσις</b></el> <el>(κλῆσις, εως) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:καλέω'><el>καλέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a calling, call</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a calling into court, legal summons, prosecution</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>an invitation</i> to a feast, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a name, appellation</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}